===Etymology===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han simp|爲|f=爫|t=丶}}. In the oracle bone script, it is an {{Han compound|又|t1=hand|象|t2=elephant|ls=ic}} — a hand holding an elephant. In ancient China, elephants were used to do manual labour, thus the compound represented "to do; to work". The {{m|mul|又}} later became {{m|mul|爪||hand; claw}}. In the seal script, the {{m|mul|象}} has been corrupted; ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' based its interpretation on the corrupted character and explained the character to be a representation of the macaque.

